============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Market Failure
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Free markets fail to allocate resources efficiently
Formula:    Social cost = private + external cost
Economist:  Arthur Pigou
Example:    Carbon emissions: negative externality requiring government intervention

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     CNN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Convolutional filters detect spatial features hierarchically
Year:        1989
Researchers: LeCun et al.
Applications:Image classification, object detection
Related:     Pooling, feature maps, ResNet

Concept:     Diffusion Model
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Learns to reverse a noise-adding process for generation
Year:        2020
Researchers: Ho et al.
Applications:Image/video/audio generation (Stable Diffusion)
Related:     DDPM, score matching, noise schedule

Concept:     Fine-tuning
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Updates pre-trained model weights on task-specific data
Year:        2018
Researchers: Howard/Ruder (ULMFiT)
Applications:Customizing LLMs, domain adaptation
Related:     Supervised fine-tuning, PEFT, LoRA

